                <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>Pomp</abbr><ex cert="low">eiae</ex></expan> Gemellae <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>Pomp</abbr><ex cert="low">eia</ex></expan> Dio<supplied reason="lost">nys</supplied>ias <lb n="4"/>et Primu<supplied reason="lost">s A</supplied><expan><abbr>ug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>ostri</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/>educat<supplied reason="lost">rici <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Vier Fragmente, davon drei aneinanderpassend. Lesung und Ergänzung weitgehend nach A. Kakoschke; J. Bartels u.a. halten educat[ores ---] für wahrscheinlicher. (B): Z. 2-5: Walser: Gemell(ae) / Pomp(eia) Di[ca]ea l(iberta) / et Primu[l]ia s(erva) / educat(rici) [A]ug(usti) n(ostri); CIL 13, 05138: Z. 2-5: Gem[in]ell[ae?] / Pomp(eia) Dig[nil]la l. / et Primu[la et Is]ias(?) / educat[rices? A]ug(usti) n(ostri); Frei-Stolba - Bielmann: Gemell[(ae)] / Pomp(eia) Dic[a]ea l(iberta) / et Primu[l]ia s(erva) / educat(ricis) [A]ug(usti) n(ostri).</p>
            </div>
